{{Lutheranism in the United States|expanded=synodical}}
The '''Association of Confessional Lutheran Churches''' ('''ACLC''') was established in the early part of the 21st century to meet the needs of [[Lutheran]] congregations that departed from the [[Evangelical Lutheran Synod]] when they considered a [[pastor]] to have been wrongly removed by that body.<ref name="history">{{cite web|url=http://theaclc.org/Informative/history_of_the_aclc.htm|title=History of the ACLC}}</ref>

==Purpose==
The root purpose of the ACLC, then, is to maintain a pool of pastors from which member congregations can call. There are five member [[Local church|churches]].

